From: LegendaryOS Build System <build@legendaryos.linux>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] block/ioprio: auto-elevate I/O priority for game processes via cgroup

Patch dodaje logikę heurystyczną do blokowego schedulera I/O:
procesy w cgroupie z atrybutem "gaming=1" (ustawianym przez gamemode/uresourced)
automatycznie otrzymują ioprio klasy RT (Real-Time) z poziomem 4.

Eliminuje stuttery spowodowane przez background I/O (systemd journal,
dnf, tracker-miner) konkurujący z ładowaniem assetów gry ze SSD/NVMe.

Działa z io.latency i io.bfq — domyślny scheduler dla LegendaryOS to BFQ.

Signed-off-by: LegendaryOS Build System <build@legendaryos.linux>
---
 block/bfq-iosched.c | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 block/Kconfig        |  6 ++++++
 2 files changed, 24 insertions(+)

diff --git a/block/bfq-iosched.c b/block/bfq-iosched.c
index aaaaaaa..ccccccc 100644
--- a/block/bfq-iosched.c
+++ b/block/bfq-iosched.c
@@ -2100,6 +2100,24 @@ static struct bfq_queue *bfq_get_queue(struct bfq_data *bfqd,
+
+/*
+ * LegendaryOS gaming I/O heuristic:
+ * If the process cgroup has gaming=1 attribute set (via gamemode / uresourced),
+ * elevate its I/O priority to RT class automatically.
+ * This prevents asset-loading stutter during active gaming sessions.
+ */
+static void legendaryos_gaming_ioprio_boost(struct bfq_queue *bfqq,
+					    struct task_struct *tsk)
+{
+	struct cgroup_subsys_state *css;
+	struct kernfs_node *kn;
+
+	css = task_css(tsk, io_cgrp_id);
+	if (!css)
+		return;
+
+	kn = kernfs_find_and_get(css->cgroup->kn, "gaming");
+	if (kn) {
+		bfqq->ioprio_class = IOPRIO_CLASS_RT;
+		bfqq->ioprio       = 4;
+		kernfs_put(kn);
+	}
+}

diff --git a/block/Kconfig b/block/Kconfig
@@ -88,3 +88,9 @@ config IOSCHED_BFQ
+config LEGENDARYOS_GAMING_IOPRIO
+	bool "Auto-elevate I/O priority for gaming cgroups (LegendaryOS)"
+	depends on IOSCHED_BFQ
+	default y
+	help
+	  Automatically sets RT ioprio for processes in cgroups with gaming=1.
+	  Set by gamemode or uresourced. Reduces asset-loading stutter.
